  <prompt>
    Run the FR-E2 acceptance grep with **production-scope-only** logic (clarified per senior review G2 / item #2, 2026-05-24). Confirm zero direct `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` references in production code OUTSIDE the explicitly-allowed boundaries:

    - **EXCLUDED from grep (legitimate references)**:
      - `Services/Ai/` (the AI internals; the boundary IS this directory)
      - `Infrastructure/DI/AiModule.cs` and related DI registration modules (the facade is wired to internals here — that's where the boundary IS)
      - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` (test code legitimately mocks AI internals; that's how unit tests work)
      - `bin/`, `obj/` (build artifacts)

    - **INCLUDED in grep (must return 0 matches)**:
      - All production code in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` not listed above
  </prompt>

  <role>.NET acceptance verifier.</role>
  <goal>Production-scope grep returns 0; test code untouched; DI module special-case acknowledged; results captured in EXECUTION-LOG.md.</goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="src">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md (FR-E2 revised)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-E2 revised">Production scope: `grep -rn "IOpenAiClient\|IPlaybookService" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --include='*.cs' --exclude-dir=Services/Ai --exclude-dir=bin --exclude-dir=obj` returns 0. Test code excluded. DI module special-cased.</constraint>
    <constraint source="senior review G2 (2026-05-24)">Test code is LEGITIMATELY out of scope; over-migration would break unit tests</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Original FR-E2 acceptance grep listed only `Services/{Finance,Workspace,Jobs,Dataverse}/` and would have missed `Api/Endpoints/`, `Api/Filters/`, `Infrastructure/DI/`. Senior review G2 surfaced that the broader scope is needed AND test code must be explicitly excluded (tests mock AI internals — that's correct). The DI module is a special-case: the facade is wired to its underlying `IOpenAiClient`/`IPlaybookService` implementations there; that's where the boundary IS, not a violation.

      Outputs of this task feed task 054 (Phase 4 gate review) which verifies Outcome E acceptance.
    </background>
    <dependencies><dependency task="052" status="not-started">Test verification stable</dependency></dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">**Primary grep (production-scope, must return 0)**: `grep -rn -E "I(OpenAiClient|PlaybookService)\b" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --include='*.cs' --exclude-dir=Services/Ai --exclude-dir=bin --exclude-dir=obj`</step>
    <step order="2">**DI module verification (informational)**: confirm `Infrastructure/DI/AiModule.cs` (or whichever module registers the facade implementations) still references the internal types — that's expected; the facade is wired there</step>
    <step order="3">**Test scope confirmation (informational)**: `grep -rn -E "I(OpenAiClient|PlaybookService)\b" tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --include='*.cs'` — non-zero is fine; tests mock these</step>
    <step order="4">**Facade reference verification**: `grep -rn "Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.PublicContracts" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — should show consumer-side adoption (non-zero matches in Finance, Workspace, Jobs, Dataverse, Filters, Endpoints)</step>
    <step order="5">Capture all grep outputs in EXECUTION-LOG.md with clear labeling (primary vs informational)</step>
    <step order="6">If primary grep returns non-zero: identify the consumer; either migrate or document justification (e.g., "internal AI helper that legitimately needs raw client — file is being relocated to Services/Ai/ in next commit")</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md</step>
  </steps>

  <tools><tool name="git">grep</tool></tools>

  <outputs><output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/EXECUTION-LOG.md (acceptance grep results, primary + informational)</output></outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
